# 1 Introduction

本报告使用 **Adult ASD screening** 数据集（文件名：`Adult_ASD.csv`）进行一个简洁的数据分析示范。该数据集包含成人 ASD（Autism Spectrum Disorder）筛查相关信息，包括：

- 10 个二元筛查条目（通常记为 A1–A10）
- 总筛查分数（total screening score）
- 人口学变量（例如年龄、性别、族裔等）
- 背景变量（例如是否黄疸、是否有 ASD 家族史）
- 结局变量：`ASD_traits`（Yes/No），表示是否被筛查为 ASD traits

**分析目标（Analysis objectives）**

1. 描述样本中 `ASD_traits`（Yes/No）的比例。
2. 比较不同 `ASD_traits` 组的总筛查分数分布是否存在明显差异。
3. 使用 logistic 回归评估：在控制年龄与性别后，总筛查分数是否仍能显著预测 `ASD_traits`。

# 2 Data loading

> 本报告默认你把数据放在项目根目录下的 `data/Adult_ASD.csv`。  
> 如果你还没建 `data/` 文件夹，请在 project root 新建一个 `data` 文件夹，并把 `Adult_ASD.csv` 放进去。

```{r packages}
library(tidyverse)
library(janitor)
library(broom)
library(knitr)
library(kableExtra)
library(here)
```

```{r read-data}
# 1) 优先从项目目录读取：project_root/data/Adult_ASD.csv
data_path1 <- here::here("data", "Adult_ASD.csv")

# 2) 如果你是在某些平台（例如自动挂载）运行，也可以直接从当前工作目录读取
data_path2 <- "Adult_ASD.csv"

# 3) 兜底：如果你在本地就是把文件放在某个绝对路径，请改成那个路径
# data_path3 <- "D:/EMORY/DATA550/project1/data/Adult_ASD.csv"

if (file.exists(data_path1)) {
  data_path <- data_path1
} else if (file.exists(data_path2)) {
  data_path <- data_path2
} else {
  stop("找不到 Adult_ASD.csv。请把文件放到 data/Adult_ASD.csv，或修改 read-data 代码块里的路径。")
}

asd_raw <- readr::read_csv(data_path, show_col_types = FALSE)

# 基础清洗：统一列名、删除可能的索引列
asd <- asd_raw %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  select(-matches("^unnamed")) 

# 把关键变量转成 factor（便于表格与建模）
# 注意：不同版本的数据集列名可能略有差别，下方会做健壮处理
# 目标：确保存在 asd_traits、sex、age_years、总分列
names(asd)
```

```{r harmonize-columns}
# 兼容不同数据版本：尝试识别“总分”列名
score_candidates <- c(
  "a10_autism_spectrum_quotient",
  "total_score",
  "aq_score",
  "screening_score"
)
score_col <- score_candidates[score_candidates %in% names(asd)][1]

if (is.na(score_col)) {
  stop("没有找到总分列。请检查数据列名（候选：a10_autism_spectrum_quotient / total_score / aq_score / screening_score），并在代码里指定。")
}

# 兼容年龄列名
age_candidates <- c("age_years", "age")
age_col <- age_candidates[age_candidates %in% names(asd)][1]
if (is.na(age_col)) stop("没有找到年龄列（候选：age_years / age）。请检查数据列名。")

# 兼容家族史列名
fam_candidates <- c("family_mem_with_asd", "family_member_with_asd", "family_asd")
fam_col <- fam_candidates[fam_candidates %in% names(asd)][1]
# 家族史不是必须，但有的话会用
if (is.na(fam_col)) fam_col <- NULL

# 兼容黄疸列名
jau_candidates <- c("jaundice")
jau_col <- jau_candidates[jau_candidates %in% names(asd)][1]
if (is.na(jau_col)) jau_col <- NULL

# 统一命名（后续代码就固定用 score / age_years）
asd <- asd %>%
  rename(
    score = all_of(score_col),
    age_years = all_of(age_col)
  )

# 关键变量类型
if (!("asd_traits" %in% names(asd))) stop("缺少结局变量 asd_traits（Yes/No）。请检查数据列名。")

asd <- asd %>%
  mutate(
    asd_traits = factor(asd_traits, levels = c("No", "Yes")),
    sex = factor(sex)
  )

# 如果存在家族史 / 黄疸，把它们转成 factor
if (!is.null(fam_col)) asd[[fam_col]] <- factor(asd[[fam_col]])
if (!is.null(jau_col)) asd[[jau_col]] <- factor(asd[[jau_col]])

glimpse(asd)
```

# 3 Descriptive results

## 3.1 Table 1: ASD traits prevalence

```{r table1}
table1 <- asd %>%
  count(asd_traits) %>%
  mutate(percent = round(100 * n / sum(n), 1))

table1 %>%
  kable(
    caption = "Table 1. Prevalence of ASD traits in the sample.",
    col.names = c("ASD_traits", "Count (n)", "Percent (%)")
  ) %>%
  kable_styling(full_width = FALSE)
```

**Table 1 description.**  
Table 1 reports the number and percentage of participants who were flagged as having ASD traits (`ASD_traits = Yes`) versus not flagged (`No`). This provides a basic overview of outcome prevalence in the dataset.

## 3.2 Table 2: Key demographics by ASD traits

```{r table2}
# 如果 sex 用 M/F 编码，male_pct 这样写；如果是 Male/Female，也能工作（只是 male_pct 会是 NA），因此做一个更稳的处理
male_indicator <- asd$sex %in% c("M", "Male", "male", "1")

table2 <- asd %>%
  group_by(asd_traits) %>%
  summarise(
    n = n(),
    age_mean = mean(age_years, na.rm = TRUE),
    age_sd = sd(age_years, na.rm = TRUE),
    score_mean = mean(score, na.rm = TRUE),
    score_sd = sd(score, na.rm = TRUE),
    male_pct = mean(male_indicator, na.rm = TRUE) * 100,
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    across(c(age_mean, age_sd, score_mean, score_sd, male_pct), ~ round(.x, 1))
  )

table2 %>%
  kable(
    caption = "Table 2. Age/sex and screening score summaries by ASD trait status.",
    col.names = c("ASD_traits", "n", "Age mean", "Age SD", "Score mean", "Score SD", "% Male")
  ) %>%
  kable_styling(full_width = FALSE)
```

**Table 2 description.**  
Table 2 summarizes age and screening score (mean/SD) by ASD trait status. If the `ASD_traits = Yes` group has a much higher average score, it suggests the screening score is strongly aligned with the outcome label.

# 4 Figure: Screening score comparison

```{r fig-score}
ggplot(asd, aes(x = asd_traits, y = score, fill = asd_traits)) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.75) +
  labs(
    title = "Screening score distribution by ASD trait status",
    x = "ASD traits flagged",
    y = "Total screening score"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
```

**Figure description.**  
This boxplot compares the distribution of total screening score between participants flagged (`Yes`) and not flagged (`No`). A higher median and upward-shifted distribution in the `Yes` group would indicate the screening score is a strong discriminator for ASD traits in this dataset.

# 5 Logistic regression analysis

我们用 logistic 回归建模 `ASD_traits (Yes/No)`，并报告 **Odds Ratio (OR)** 与 95% CI。  
为了保持模型可解释性，先使用一个简洁模型：`score + age_years + sex`。

```{r glm-fit}
fit <- glm(
  asd_traits ~ score + age_years + sex,
  data = asd,
  family = binomial()
)

model_tab <- broom::tidy(fit, conf.int = TRUE, exponentiate = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(
    term = recode(
      term,
      `(Intercept)` = "Intercept",
      score = "Screening score (per 1 point)",
      age_years = "Age (per 1 year)"
    )
  ) %>%
  select(term, estimate, conf.low, conf.high, p.value) %>%
  mutate(
    across(c(estimate, conf.low, conf.high), ~ round(.x, 2)),
    p.value = signif(p.value, 3)
  )

model_tab %>%
  kable(
    caption = "Table 3. Logistic regression results (Odds Ratios) for ASD traits (Yes vs No).",
    col.names = c("Predictor", "OR", "CI (low)", "CI (high)", "p-value")
  ) %>%
  kable_styling(full_width = FALSE)
```

**Model/Table description.**  
Table 3 reports adjusted associations with `ASD_traits`. An OR > 1 for the screening score means that higher score is associated with higher odds of being flagged for ASD traits, after adjusting for age and sex.

# 6 Conclusion

本报告围绕三个目标完成了一个基础但完整的分析流程：  
(1) 描述 `ASD_traits` 的样本比例；(2) 使用表格与箱线图展示筛查分数在两组间的差异；(3) 通过 logistic 回归评估筛查分数在控制年龄与性别后的预测作用。  
后续可以进一步扩展：加入更多协变量（例如族裔、家族史、黄疸等），并进行模型诊断与预测性能评估（如 ROC/AUC）。
